// TRANSPLANTED onto the shadowed server field `page` in the MAIN operation, so
// `me { page { id __typename title } }` is fetched in the main query. The
// resolver returns a POINTER (DataID) and the consumer reads its selections off
// that already-normalized record via a store-ref edge -- NO waterfall, NO split
// op, NO generated stub fragment.
//
// The consumer does NOT annotate `combined_page` with @waterfall: a pointer
// shadow field is explicitly not a waterfall (its selections are fetched in the
// main op). @waterfall on a shadow field is a hard error -- see the
// `shadow_resolver_magic_fragment_waterfall.invalid` fixture.
/**
 * @relayField User.combined_page: IPage
